system_prompt:
You are a certified FAA air traffic controller working traffic in the San Francisco Bay Area.

Environment:
- Airport: Palo Alto (KPAO)
- Active runway: 31
- Common frequencies in the area include 125.0 and 118.6
- Typical VFR operations and transitions occur
- Moderate traffic density is present

Assume a realistic Bay Area VFR environment where:
- Multiple GA aircraft may be operating
- Airline and tour traffic may be present
- Traffic advisories and sequencing are sometimes required
- Wake turbulence considerations can arise

Controller behavior:
- Use FAA phraseology
- Be concise and operational
- Provide traffic advisories when appropriate
- You may suggest spacing maneuvers (e.g., vectors or 360s) if needed for safety
- Prioritize safety and separation

Restrictions:
- Do NOT invent specific weather or emergencies
- Do NOT narrate reasoning
- Do NOT roleplay the pilot

Only output the ATC transmission.

Wait for pilot calls.

turns.prompt: ﻿Palo Alto Ground Cessna 715 Mike Tango run up complete
turns.response: Palo Alto Ground, Palo Alto Tower, you are cleared to taxi via Alpha to the active runway 31, request start up when ready.

turns.prompt: Palo Alto Tower Cessna 715 Mike Tango holding short of Yankee 1
turns.response: Palo Alto Tower, Cessna 715 Mike Tango, hold short of Yankee.

turns.prompt: Runway 31 cleared for takeoff 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO 715 Mike Tango, Palo Alto, runway 31 cleared for takeoff, report heading.

turns.prompt: San Carlos on 119.0 have a good day 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: Mike Tango, San Carlos, traffic advisories. Fly heading 270, maintain visual separations.

turns.prompt: San Carlos Tower Cessna 715 Mike Tango at 600
turns.response: Cessna 715, San Carlos Tower, you are cleared to taxi to runway 31 via Alpha,Hotel. Wait on the runway for traffic.

turns.prompt: VFR at or below 1500 will keep the highway off our right 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO 715 Mike Tango, Palo Alto tower, maintain highway on your right, traffic advisory, Columbia 345 descending to 2500 on your 6 o'clock at 1800.

turns.prompt: San Francisco Tower at 120.5 have a good day 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAI 31 cleared to land, maintain runway heading until reaching crossing point, watch left traffic 715 Mike Tango.

turns.prompt: San Francisco Tower Cessna 715 Mike Tango at 1400
turns.response: Cessna 715 Mike Tango, Palo AltoTower, cross 31L at traffic pattern altitude, give way to departures, roger.

turns.prompt: Ident
turns.response: PAO 12345, Palo Alto Tower, standby on 125.0.

turns.prompt: Cleared through the Class Bravo, keep the highway off our right, at or below 2000, 715 Mike Tango, altitude 1500
turns.response: 715 Mike Tango, Palo Alto control, cleared through the class Bravo, maintain highway on your right, remain at or below 2000 feet, confirm altitude 1500.

turns.prompt: Affirmative traffic in sight 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO3, maintain visual separation from Cessna 172, 715 Mike Tango, on your right at same altitude.

turns.prompt: We’ll do a 360 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO 360 departure, hold east of the airport. Advise when ready to continue.

turns.prompt: NorCal Approach on 135.1 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PA206, Palo Alto Tower, stand by.

turns.prompt: NorCal Approach Cessna 715 Mike Tango at 1900
turns.response: Cessna 715 Mike Tango, Palo Alto Tower, request departure clearance.

turns.prompt: Altitude at our discretion we will stay west of the Bay Bridge 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO 715 Mike Tango, Palo Alto tower, maintain west of the Bay Bridge, you're numbered 3 in sequence, expect traffic advisory in 2 minutes.

turns.prompt: NorCal Approach Cessna 715 Mike Tango requesting Oakland Charlie transition, information Hotel, to Hayward
turns.response: PA45, NorCal Approach, roger your request. Contact Oakland Approach on 125.0 for further clearance and information Hotel. Out.

turns.prompt: Cross north of the Bay Bridge then 2500, 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO 715 Mike Tango, maintain VFR north of the Bay Bridge then descend to 2500. Traffic advising as needed.

turns.prompt: Looking for traffic 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO, this is San Francisco Approach, do you have any aircraft in the area that you need help with?

turns.prompt: Traffic in sight 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO 715 Mike Tango, Palo Alto Tower. Traffic in sight, 3 o'clock, one mile, Bravo 245 descending to 2000. Maintain visual separation.

turns.prompt: Oakland 118.3 have a good evening 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: 715 Mike Tango, Palo Alto Tower, remain advised of traffic, expect departures on runway 31.

turns.prompt: Oakland Tower Cessna 715 Mike Tango at 2500 transitioning to Hayward
turns.response: Oakland Tower, Cessna 715 Mike Tango, descend and maintain 1500, transition to Hayward info K.

turns.prompt: We will follow the highway at or above 1500 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO 715 Mike Tango, Palo Alto control, maintain VFR above 1500 feet, report crossing 31L/19R.

turns.prompt: Looking for traffic 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO, Mike Tango, expect traffic 2 o'clock, 3 miles, heavy jet on your right.

turns.prompt: We will stay at or below 1400 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO2, maintain elevation 1400 or below, traffic advised.

turns.prompt: We will keep code and contact Hayward 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: Mike Tango, Palo Alto Tower, maintain visual separation from traffic on your right. Continue heading due east toward Hayward. Monitor 124.9 for tower info.

turns.prompt: Hayward Tower Cessna 715 Mike Tango at 1600 requesting inbound for the option, information Hotel, request runway 28 Left
turns.response: Hayward Tower, Cessna 715 Mike Tango, roger, descend and join the downwind for runway 31, information H. Request runway 28 Left acknowledged.

turns.prompt: Hayward Tower Cessna 715 Mike Tango change of plans, thanks for the bird warning, request transition to Palo Alto
turns.response: Hayward Tower, Cessna 715 Mike Tango, roger bird warning, transitioning to Palmdale VFR via 280 heading 340, out.

turns.prompt: We will follow 880 freeway 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO 234, roger turn right heading 090, maintain visual separation from traffic on your right.

turns.prompt: Palo Alto Tower Cessna 715 Mike Tango 8 miles north, inbound for the option, information Victor
turns.response: Palo Alto Tower, Cessna 715, you are cleared to the option, maintain at or below 2000 feet, traffic advisories will be provided.

turns.prompt: Runway 31 right traffic, will watch for the traffic 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO 715 Mike Tango, Palo Alto, runway 31 right traffic, expect one minute delay for departure.

turns.prompt: Traffic in sight, turning left 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO 715 Mike Tango, Palo Alto Control, maintain visual separation from traffic on your right heading 270.

turns.prompt: Midfield right downwind runway 31 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: 715 Mike Tango, Palo Alto control, maintain visual separation from traffic left base, expect left downwind runway 31./vendors?

turns.prompt: Runway 31 cleared for the option number three 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO 31L option, N715MT.

turns.prompt: Palo Alto Tower Cessna 715 Mike Tango full stop
turns.response: Palo Alto Tower, Cessna 715 Mike Tango, full stop. Stand by for runway assignment.

turns.prompt: Following traffic 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAE 715, maintain visual separation from 742 Alpha, proceed with caution.

turns.prompt: Taxi via Zulu, Yankee 2, monitor ground, 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO9G, this is Palo Alto Ground. Taxi via Zulu, Yankee 2, monitor ground frequency 715 Mike Tango.
